Sunday Aborisade and Leke Baiyewu, Abuja The Senate on Tuesday adjourned legislative activities to mourn the sudden death of one of its members, Senator Ignatius Longjan. The senator, until his demise, represented the people of Plateau South Senatorial District. He died on Sunday, February 10, 2020. The Senate Leader, Yahaya Abdullahi, who came under Order 43 of Senate rules, expressed grief over Longjan’s death. He said, “…We also recall that he was a one-time deputy governor of Plateau State which is a no mean achievement. “It is our convention that the Senate observes a minute silence and adjourn plenary till Wednesday February 12, 2020,in honour of our colleague Ignatius Longjan.” The Deputy Senate President, Ovie Omo-Agege, who presided over the session, announced that the chamber would suspend plenary and other legislative activities in honour of the deceased lawmaker. He also said that the Wednesday plenary would be devoted to celebrate the late Senator Benjamin Uwajumogu, who died in December last year. He said, “Our hearts are very heavy today. This is one death too many just as we have been grieving the loss of another of our dear friend and bosom colleague, Benjamin   Uwajumogu who left us about two months ago, today it is another. “It is very painful, he was a fine gentleman, a man who rendered selfless service to his state as deputy governor and to his senatorial district as senator representing Plateau South.” Also, in the House of Representatives on Tuesday, members adjourned plenary in honour of Longjan. Members of the House led by the Speaker, Femi Gbajabiamila, observed a minute silence in honour of Longjan. Copyright PUNCH.
